        <bioghist>
            <p>The Butler mansion was designed by architect Stanford White and built by the architectural firm McKim, Mead and White; construction began in 1896. Its first occupants were the George Williams family, who commissioned the home. In 1908, the mansion was purchased by Edward Butler Sr., founder of what is now known as The Buffalo News. The neighboring Metcalfe house was built in 1884 by McKim, Mead and White for Erzelia F. Metcalfe and her son James S. Metcalfe and was demolished in 1980.</p>
        </bioghist>
